\title{gpbiometrics: Process, Audit, Plot, and Report Gazepoint Biometrics Data}
\description{
\code{gpbiometrics} provides helper functions for importing, checking,
preprocessing, summarising, diagnosing, plotting, and reporting Gazepoint
Biometrics exports. It is designed for reproducible offline workflows
involving physiological, response-channel, event-marker, and timing data
exported alongside Gazepoint eye-tracking recordings.
}
\details{
The package supports common Gazepoint biometric channels, including GSR/EDA,
heart rate, interbeat interval or RR-style intervals, engagement dial, and
TTL markers. It provides functions for folder-level import, data-summary
import, schema and timebase detection, active-channel detection, column
validation, missingness audits, signal-quality audits, sampling and timing
audits, dropout and flatline flagging, baseline correction, smoothing, window
summaries, TTL event extraction, biometric-to-gaze synchronisation, exclusion
recommendations, workflow diagnostics, report-ready tables, cautious methods
text, lightweight report generation, and base-R diagnostic plotting.

Schema and timing helpers include
\code{standardise_gazepoint_biometric_names()},
\code{detect_gazepoint_biometric_schema()},
\code{detect_gazepoint_time_columns()}, and
\code{detect_gazepoint_biometric_timebase()}. Signal-availability and quality
helpers include \code{summarise_gazepoint_biometric_validity()},
\code{flag_gazepoint_biometric_dropouts()}, \code{audit_gazepoint_gsr_quality()},
\code{audit_gazepoint_hr_quality()}, \code{audit_gazepoint_engagement_dial()}, and
\code{audit_gazepoint_ibi_quality()}.

Preprocessing and summary helpers include
\code{baseline_correct_gazepoint_gsr()},
\code{baseline_correct_gazepoint_hr()}, \code{smooth_gazepoint_biometrics()},
\code{convert_gazepoint_gsr_to_conductance()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_gsr_windows()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_hr_windows()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_engagement_windows()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_dial_windows()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_ibi_windows()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_gsr_tonic_phasic()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_multimodal_windows()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_ibi_hrv_windows()}, and
\code{summarise_gazepoint_full_biometric_windows()}.

Synchronisation, modelling, workflow, and reporting helpers include
\code{sync_gazepoint_biometrics_with_gaze()},
\code{join_gazepoint_biometrics_to_master()},
\code{join_gazepoint_biometrics_to_gp3tools()},
\code{prepare_gazepoint_multimodal_model_data()},
\code{run_gazepoint_biometrics_workflow()},
\code{summarise_gazepoint_biometrics_workflow()},
\code{diagnose_gazepoint_biometrics_workflow()},
\code{create_gazepoint_biometrics_checklist()},
\code{create_gazepoint_biometrics_methods_text()},
\code{create_gazepoint_biometrics_report_tables()},
\code{write_gazepoint_biometrics_report_tables()}, and
\code{create_gazepoint_biometrics_report()}. Diagnostic plotting helpers include
\code{plot_gazepoint_biometric_signals()} and
\code{plot_gazepoint_biometric_quality()}.

The package treats biometric signals conservatively. GSR/EDA is handled as an
electrodermal activity or arousal-related signal rather than emotional
valence. Heart-rate summaries should be interpreted relative to baseline,
artefact handling, and task context. Raw Gazepoint \code{HRV} columns should be
treated as validity or vendor flags unless independent documentation proves
otherwise. IBI-derived HRV-style summaries should be computed only from
genuine interbeat interval or RR-style interval columns. Eye-tracking
measures, when combined with biometric data, should be interpreted as
indicators of visual attention rather than direct evidence of cognition,
scrutiny, or evaluation.
}
